description: The Swiss-owned, so-called 'English' Cemetery in Florence, Italy, is in great need of restoration. Famous poets, like Elizabeth Barrett Browning, Walter Savage Landor and Arthur Hugh Clough, and sculptors, like Hiram Powers and Joel T. Hart, are buried here. Also many who were against slavery. This weblog seeks to raise interest, participation, funds.
title: 'English' Cemetery and its Library, Florence

description:
I’m not crazy about seafood.  I don’t eat cheese or milk-based foods.  And I don’t like most beans.  But I love a great meal!!!  Since living here in Sendai I’ve come across a number of restaurants, bakeries, and assorted other eateries that are perfect for me and my pickiness.  
My aim with this blog is twofold:
1) to help others like me (and normal people, too) find satisfying meals,                
2) for others to help me by suggesting new places that I might like.
title: A Picky Eater’s Guide to Sendai Grub

description: Political Horizons is an attempt to develop a civil conversation on political questions outside the proverbial smoke-filled rooms. Although much practical work takes place at the political center, many of the best ideas are... way out there. Another thing about our metaphorical horizon is that it is a circle -- all points are equally far from the center, and connected to each other, in contrast to the usual political "spectrum."
title: Political Horizons
